This paper deals with the problem of person re-identification in visual surveillance, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves learning to predict edge weights in a graph matching problem, which is a common approach in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of visual patterns, which is a common topic in multimedia (cs.MM) research. Finally, the paper deals with the challenges of maintaining consistent matches across different camera views, which is a security and privacy concern (cs.CR).
